FBIS4-34843 "drlat122_m_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-122 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 Brazil PRC Health Minister Visits Brasilia PRC Health Minister Visits Brasilia PY2406005294 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 2200 GMT 23 Jun 94 PY2406005294 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network Portuguese BFN [Report by Flavio Figueiredo from the Health Ministry in Brasilia] [Text] The Brazilian Government may import medicines from the PRC. This was discussed today by Chinese Public Health Minister Chen Minzhang and Brazilian Health Ministry officials. The Chinese guarantee that the medicines will arrive in Brazil at prices below domestic ones. Minister Chen says China produces medicines with lower costs because they are produced on a large scale and the raw materials are obtained through advanced technologies. Health Secretary Adney Moraes said the import of Chinese medicines is a way to solve the problem of high medicine prices in Brazil. The Brazilian Government will examine the feasibility of the Chinese proposal.
